APPENDIX F: ADDITIVE MANUFACTURING PHYSICS

F.1 Laser-Material Interaction and Melt Pool Dynamics

Laser absorption in metal powder: $q(r) = \frac{2P}{\pi w^2} \exp\left(-\frac{2r^2}{w^2}\right)$

Melt pool dimensions estimated by Rosenthal solution:

T - T_0 = \frac{P}{2\pi k r} \exp\left(-\frac{v(x+r)}{2\alpha}\right)

But for AM, detailed CFD models (FLOW-3D) used.

F.2 Cooling Rate Calculations for PSM-1B

Cooling rate $dT/dt$ determines Al₁₃Fe₄ size:

\frac{dT}{dt} = \frac{2\pi k (T - T_0)^2}{P \eta}

For P=300 W, k=120 W/m·K, T=700°C, T_0=200°C, η=0.3: $dT/dt \approx 10^6$ K/s, sufficient for <200 nm intermetallics.

F.3 Powder Flow in Reduced Gravity (DEM simulations)

Discrete Element Method (DEM) simulates powder spreading:

m_i \frac{d\mathbf{v}_i}{dt} = \sum \mathbf{F}_{contact} + m_i \mathbf{g} + \mathbf{F}_{cohesive}

Cohesive forces (van der Waals) dominate at 1/6 g. Gas-flow-assisted delivery adds drag force $\mathbf{F}_{drag} = \frac{1}{2}\rho C_d A |\mathbf{u}-\mathbf{v}|(\mathbf{u}-\mathbf{v})$.

F.4 Residual Stress Modeling

Thermal stress during AM:

\sigma_{res} = \frac{E \alpha \Delta T}{1-\nu} \times \text{constraint factor}

For PSM-1 with preheat 200°C, ΔT=500°C, E=75 GPa, α=22e-6, ν=0.335: $\sigma_{res} \approx \frac{75e9 \times 22e-6 \times 500}{0.665} = \frac{825e6}{0.665} = 1.24$ GPa—exceeds yield, hence plastic relaxation occurs, leaving ~100 MPa.

