APPENDIX G: STATISTICAL METHODS FOR QUALIFICATION

G.1 A-Basis and B-Basis Calculations

A-basis: 95% survival with 99% confidence. For normal distribution, A-basis = $\bar{x} - k_A s$, where $k_A$ depends on sample size n.

For n=100, $k_A \approx 2.33$ (from MIL-HDBK-17). B-basis (90% confidence): $k_B \approx 1.93$ for n=100.

G.2 Weibull Analysis for Fatigue Data

Three-parameter Weibull:

P(N) = 1 - \exp\left[-\left(\frac{N - N_0}{\theta}\right)^\beta\right]

Parameters estimated by maximum likelihood. Fatigue limit often modeled by staircase method.

G.3 Digital Twin Validation and Uncertainty Quantification

Bayesian calibration of model parameters using experimental data:

p(\theta|D) \propto p(D|\theta) p(\theta)

Posterior predictive distribution for virtual tests:

p(y_{new}|D) = \int p(y_{new}|\theta) p(\theta|D) d\theta

