H.3 Thermal Cycling Accelerated Test Derivation

Coffin-Manson: $\Delta \epsilon_p = C (N_f)^{-c}$

For thermal cycling, $\Delta \epsilon \approx \Delta \alpha \Delta T$. Acceleration factor $AF = (N_{f,accel}/N_{f,real}) = (\Delta T_{real}/\Delta T_{accel})^{-c}$.

With c=0.5 (typical), $\Delta T_{real}=300$ K, $\Delta T_{accel}=500$ K (using faster cycles but same ΔT? Actually accelerating frequency, not ΔT). For frequency acceleration, Miner's rule applies.

H.4 Regolith Abrasion Test Setup

· Apparatus: Vacuum chamber with dust injector, sample stage, laser Doppler velocimeter
· Dust: JSC-1A, <100 μm, baked to remove volatiles
· Velocity: 50 m/s (supersonic nozzle)
· Angles: 30°, 60°, 90°
· Duration: 1, 10, 100 hours
· Measurements: Mass loss, profilometry, SEM, optical transmission

